Why aren't all grocery stores doing this?! This IGA supermarket is providing shoppers with super fresh and organic veggies grown right over their heads! The store is also cutting its water waste by providing thirsty plants with water collected from the store's air conditioning system instead of letting it pour down the drain. This initiative's not only a super sustainable way to reduce the miles used to transport crops across the country, green roofs also help absorb greenhouse gases and fight climate change! Want in on this action? Grow your own food or shop from local farmers markets to get your food sustainably!
